Package: significantEarthquakes
Type: Package
Title: Working With NOAA Significant Earthquakes Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "EL", "Williams",
      email = "placeholder@example.com",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: A package that can be used to clean and visualize the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration's 
    significant earthquakes database. Significant earthquakes are those that meet at least one of the following criteria.
    Cause moderate damage costing $1 million or more, results in 10 or more deaths, has a magnitude of 7.5 or greater, has
    a modifed Mercali intensity of X or greater, or the earthquake generated a tsunami. Earthquakes are recoreded beginning
    in 2150 B.C. so data cleaning in this package accounts for era (BC or AD).
